  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>The number 7 is special, because 7 is 111 written in base 2, and 11 written in base 6 (i.e. $7_{10} = {11}_6 = {111}_2$). In other words, 7 is a repunit in at least two bases $b > 1$.</p>\n<p>We shall call a positive integer with this property a strong repunit. It can be verified that there are 8 strong repunits below 50: {1, 7, 13, 15, 21, 31, 40, 43}. Furthermore, the sum of all strong repunits below 1000 equals 15864.</p>\n<p>Find the sum of all strong repunits below ${10}^{12}$.</p>\n</section>",
